llm_answer:
The X‑band resonance field for a radical with $g=2.005$ and $\nu=9.5\;{\rm GHz}$ is  

\[
B_0=\frac{h\nu}{g\mu_B}
    =\frac{(6.626\times10^{-34}\ {\rm J\,s})(9.5\times10^9\ {\rm s^{-1}})}
           {(2.005)(9.274\times10^{-24}\ {\rm J\,T^{-1}})}
    \approx 0.3385\ {\rm T}
    = 338.5\ {\rm mT}.
\]

The two hyperfine lines are separated in frequency by $\Delta\nu =280\ {\rm MHz}$.  
The corresponding separation in magnetic field is  

\[
\Delta B=\frac{h\Delta\nu}{g\mu_B}
       =\frac{(6.626\times10^{-34}\ {\rm J\,s})(280\times10^6\ {\rm s^{-1}})}
              {(2.005)(9.274\times10^{-24}\ {\rm J\,T^{-1}})}
       \approx 9.97\ {\rm mT}.
\]

Thus each line is displaced by half this amount from $B_0$.  
The higher‑field line is

\[
B_{\text{high}}
  = B_0 + \frac{\Delta B}{2}
  = 338.5\ {\rm mT} + 4.99\ {\rm mT}
  \approx \boxed{343.5}\ {\rm mT}.

