\[
n_{\ce{KOH}} = C_{\ce{KOH}}\;V_{\ce{KOH}}
               = (0.0400\;\text{mol L}^{-1})(6.81\;\text{mL})(10^{-3}\;\text{L mL}^{-1})
               = 2.724\times10^{-4}\;\text{mol}
\]

**Step 2 – moles of polymer chains**

\[
n_{\text{chains}} = n_{\ce{KOH}} = 2.724\times10^{-4}\;\text{mol}
\]

(The polymer is assumed to have one carboxylic acid end group per chain.)

**Step 3 – average molar mass (Mn)**

\[
M_n = \frac{m_{\text{PLA}}}{n_{\text{chains}}}
     = \frac{0.1619\;\text{g}}{2.724\times10^{-4}\;\text{mol}}
     = 5.95\times10^{2}\;\text{g mol}^{-1}
\]

---

